@startuml sequence_pos_transaction
!theme plain
title Sequence: POS Transaction Flow (UI -> API -> Kafka -> Consumers)

actor User
participant "React\nPosTerminal" as FE
participant "FastAPI\nEvent Routes" as API
participant "Kafka\npos-events" as K
participant "Consumer\nPython" as CPY
participant "Consumer\nNode" as CN
participant "Plugins" as Plugins
participant "PostgreSQL\nevent_log" as PG
participant "API\n/webhook/mock" as Webhook

== Start Transaction ==
User -> FE : Click "Start Transaction"
FE -> API : POST /pos/transaction/start\nBearer token\n{ store_id, terminal_id }
API -> API : get_current_user (JWT)
API -> API : Build transaction.started event\nuuid transaction_id
API -> K : produce transaction.started
K --> API : ack
API --> FE : 200 { transaction_id, event }
FE --> User : Show transaction_id, next step

== Customer / Items / Subtotal / Pay ==
User -> FE : Identify customer
FE -> API : POST /pos/transaction/customer\n{ transaction_id, customer_id, customer_name }
API -> K : produce customer.identified
API --> FE : 200 { event }

User -> FE : Add item(s)
FE -> API : POST /pos/transaction/item (per item)\n{ transaction_id, item_name, sku, quantity, unit_price, category }
API -> K : produce item.added
API --> FE : 200 { line_total, event }

User -> FE : Subtotal
FE -> API : POST /pos/transaction/subtotal\n{ transaction_id, subtotal, tax_rate }
API -> K : produce transaction.subtotal
API --> FE : 200 { total, tax, event }

User -> FE : Pay
FE -> API : POST /pos/transaction/pay\n{ transaction_id, payment_method, amount_due }
API -> K : produce payment.completed
API --> FE : 200 { receipt_number, event }
FE --> User : Show receipt / done

== Asynchronous Consumer Processing (per event) ==
K -> CPY : consume message (any event)
K -> CN  : consume message (same event, different group)
CPY -> CPY : ConfigStore.get_plugin_config(plugin_name)
CPY -> CPY : For each plugin: matches(event, settings)?
CPY -> Plugins : handle(event, settings) with retry 1s,2s,4s
Plugins -> Webhook : HTTP Call: POST target_url (e.g. /webhook/mock)
Webhook --> Plugins : 200
Plugins -> K : Event Publisher: produce pos-derived-events (if payment.completed)
CPY -> PG : INSERT event_log (event_type, transaction_id, payload, plugin_name, consumer)
note right: On final plugin failure -> produce to pos-events-dlq

CN -> CN : Same flow: config, match, handle, event_log / DLQ

== Event Log View ==
User -> FE : Open "Events" tab
FE -> API : GET /events?limit=50\nBearer
API -> PG : SELECT * FROM event_log ORDER BY processed_at DESC LIMIT ?
PG --> API : rows
API --> FE : 200 [ events ]
FE --> User : Display event log

@enduml
